# ============================================================================
# HTTP Test File: Overdue Functionality Testing
# Purpose: Test overdue functionality through API endpoints
# Instructions: Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tool
# ============================================================================

### 1. Login as Owner to get auth token
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "owner@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Store the token from response and use it in subsequent requests
### Replace YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN with actual token from login response

### 2. Get Collection Dashboard Data (should show overdue info)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/owner/reports/collection-summary
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN

### 3. Get Tenant Installments (to see overdue installments)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/owner/reports/tenant/TENANT_ID/installments
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN

### 4. Get Tenant Payment History
GET http://localhost:8080/api/owner/reports/tenant/TENANT_ID/payment-history
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN

### 5. Test Other Charges Overdue
GET http://localhost:8080/api/owner/other-charges
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN

### 6. Login as Tenant to see overdue from tenant perspective
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "tenant@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 7. Get Tenant Dashboard (should show overdue count)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tenant/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer TENANT_AUTH_TOKEN

### 8. Get Tenant Payment Plan (should show overdue installments)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tenant/payment-plan
Authorization: Bearer TENANT_AUTH_TOKEN